Package: erlangR
Type: Package
Title: Erlang-A Queueing Models for Staffing Decisions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Package", "Owner", email = "owner@example.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = "Placeholder -- replace with your name and email"),
    person("Claude", "(Anthropic)", role = "ctb",
           comment = "Initial implementation"))
Description: Exact analytic performance measures for the Erlang-A (M/M/n+M)
    queue: Poisson arrivals, exponential service times, n parallel agents,
    and exponentially distributed caller patience. The central quantity is
    P(abandon | number of agents), intended to drive staffing decisions
    through expected-loss analysis rather than service-level targets.
    Provides maximum-likelihood fitting from interval-aggregated contact
    centre data in the familiar fit/predict/plot workflow, Erlang B and
    Erlang C as limiting cases, an event-based simulator for validation and
    experiment design, and a worked half-hour example dataset.
